# Folder-scoped credentials and install state — never commit these.
.config/
.claude/
.agents/
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Team-specific infra knowledge. Each team fills in its own version from
# the committed <topic>.example.md templates; the filled-in copies are
# local-only so rca-assist can be distributed as a generic product.
infra-knowledge/*.md
!infra-knowledge/README.md
!infra-knowledge/*.example.md

# Per-incident folders under incidents/<YYYY-MM-DD>-<slug>/. Each
# contains the RCA writeup, original alert text, learnings, and raw
# evidence (logs, metric snapshots) — all of which reference real
# service names, trace IDs, IPs, and timelines that shouldn't be
# shared publicly. The convention itself (incidents/README.md and
# any incidents/*.example/ reference folders) stays tracked so the
# layout travels with the skill.
/incidents/*/
!/incidents/*.example/
!/incidents/*.example/**

# Legacy: RCA artifacts that used to land at the repo root before the
# incidents/ convention. Kept ignored for back-compat with older clones.
# Anchored to root so skill-reference filenames starting with "rca-"
# (like rca-doc-template.md) stay tracked.
/RCA-*.md
/rca-*.md

# Cloudflare Pages local cache
.wrangler/
